 You can run the code by calling: blender -P
AnimateGrains7.py -- --directory="<full path to simulation data>"
--start=<first timestep to render> --finish=<last timestep to render>
--particles=<number of particles in simulation -r = 'yes'

You will need to install blender and numpy as: sudo apt-get install
blender numpy


Pierre line  

blender -P AnimateGrains.py -- --directory="/home/prognon/SD_parallel/data/plan/" --start=1 --finish=5 --particles=611
